  "content": "In many countries, austerity is a hard sell. Loans from the International Monetary Fund  IMF  can provide economic stabilization and financial support for developing countries with conditions. Recipients typically need to restructure their economies, moving away from public sector services in the effort to foster market competition and private-sector business.",
